  "text": "Spectral methods have become standard techniques in algebraic graph theory; see, e.g., [CITATION_1] . The most widely used techniques utilize eigenvalues and eigenvectors of the adjacency matrix of the graph. More recently, the interest has shifted somewhat to the spectrum of the closely related Laplacian. In fact, Mohar [CITATION_2] claims that the Laplacian spectrum is more fundamental than this of the adjacency matrix.",
